<div><font face="courier new, monospace" size="1">                          Comma-delimited list of devices and/or CIDR</font></div><div><font face="courier new, monospace" size="1">                          notation of networks to use for MPI communication</font></div>
<div><font face="courier new, monospace" size="1">                          (e.g., &quot;eth0,<a href="http://192.168.0.0/16">192.168.0.0/16</a>&quot;).  Mutually exclusive</font></div><div><font face="courier new, monospace" size="1">                          with btl_tcp_if_exclude.</font></div>
<div><font face="courier new, monospace" size="1">                 MCA btl: parameter &quot;btl_tcp_if_exclude&quot; (current value:</font></div><div><font face="courier new, monospace" size="1">                          &quot;<a href="http://127.0.0.1/8,sppp">127.0.0.1/8,sppp</a>&quot;, <span style="background-color:rgb(255,255,0)">data source: default</span>, level: 1</font></div>
<div><font face="courier new, monospace" size="1">                          user/basic, type: string)</font></div><div><font face="courier new, monospace" size="1">                          Comma-delimited list of devices and/or CIDR</font></div>
<div><font face="courier new, monospace" size="1">                          notation of networks to NOT use for MPI</font></div><div><font face="courier new, monospace" size="1">                          communication -- all devices not matching these</font></div>
<div><font face="courier new, monospace" size="1">                          specifications will be used (e.g.,</font></div><div><font face="courier new, monospace" size="1">                          &quot;eth0,<a href="http://192.168.0.0/16">192.168.0.0/16</a>&quot;).  If set to a non-default</font></div>
<div><font face="courier new, monospace" size="1">                          value, it is mutually exclusive with</font></div><div><font face="courier new, monospace" size="1">                          btl_tcp_if_include.</font></div>
